{
  "id": "c862f7e16a0a4620",
  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/skelar/29273fae-d081-4ede-9903-e56492bafaaa/application",
    "company": "skelar",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "c862f7e16a0a4620",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/3a2721ac-0cf6-4bb5-a785-483b8d1018c3/Ashby_header.png]\n\nSKELAR is a venture builder that creates international IT companies according to venture capital investment guidelines. Together with our co-founders, we assemble solid and efficient teams to launch tech businesses that will succeed globally.\n\n\nRight now, we’re looking for a Middle/Senior User Acquisition Manager who will help lead one of the key marketing streams on Meta for our partner company, Duomo.\n\nDuomo is an app rooted in Christian values, helping people turn Scripture into daily habits and inner peace. We’re building a leading Christian-tech product for people seeking spiritual renewal.\n\n\nYOU WILL HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY TO:\n\n— See the results of your work in real time\n— Rapidly grow in performance marketing\n— Help build the #1 business in the niche\n— Learn how tech businesses are built — directly from the source\n— Work with a team of highly driven, results-focused people\n\n\nWHAT YOU WILL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR:\n\n— Creating and executing the user acquisition strategy on Meta\n— Managing marketing campaigns to hit target financial KPIs, evaluating performance both on top-level metrics (CPM, CTR, CR, CPA) and deeper metrics (funnel conversion, LTV, ROI)\n— Driving process automation strategy together with analytics and MarTech teams\n— Closely collaborating with creative and product marketing teams to drive growth of your stream\n\n\nWHAT YOU NEED TO SUCCEED IN THIS ROLE:\n\n— 2+ years of experience in performance marketing, driving user acquisition on paid channels (Meta, TikTok, Google Media)\n— Experience managing budgets of $300,000+ per month\n— Hands-on experience with automating user acquisition processes\n— Strong structure and organization: you love documenting and testing everything, validating every possible hypothesis, and won’t stop until you find the most effective solution\n— Strong analytical mindset: you enjoy working with data, spotting patterns, and drawing conclusions\n— Comfort working in uncertainty, fast learning, and adaptability\n— English level: B2+\n\nWhy Duomo\n\n— You’ll work on a product with a clear mission and real values.\n— You’ll help us transition from a content-rich app into a truly connected spiritual platform.\n— You’ll be early enough to influence how product is done at Duomo long-term.\n\nWhat we offer:\n\n— Competitive salary;\n— Significant impact on a rapidly growing business and contribution to how it shapes up;\n— Ample career opportunities for ambitious growth and development;\n— A possibility to attend internal, external courses, seminars and the access to a corporate library;\n— Comfortable working environment. We provide all necessary work equipment for your role and serve complimentary breakfasts, lunches, and snacks in the office;\n— 20 days of paid vacation, medical insurance and a variety of sports activities available for employees inside and outside the office.\n\nLet's build the next big everything together!\n\n[https://app.ashbyhq.com/api/images/user-content/586ac3cb-f234-40cf-96fd-3daae8c41309/bf8afb62-59f5-436b-b500-74f06bd0bb6e/Ashby_footer_eng.png]",
